definitions.definition: A small entrance hall , antechamber , passage , or room between the outer door and the main hall , lobby , or interior of a building .

subdefinitions.definition: A large entrance hall in a temple or palace .
An enclosed entrance at the end of a railway passenger car .

definitions.definition: Any of a number of body cavities or channels , serving as or resembling an entrance to another bodily space.

subdefinitions.definition: The central cavity of the bony labyrinth of the inner ear or the parts (such as the saccule and utricle ) of the membranous labyrinth that it contains.
The part of the left ventricle below the aortic orifice .
The part of the mouth outside the teeth and gums .
Clipping of vulval vestibule : the space in the vulva between the labia minora and into which both the urethra and vagina open.

main_definition: ( architecture ) A small entrance hall , antechamber , passage , or room between the outer door and the main hall , lobby , or interior of a building . [from the 17th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( anatomy ) Any of a number of body cavities or channels , serving as or resembling an entrance to another bodily space. [from the 18th c.]
